---
import PageLayout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import WPPageHero from '~/components/wordpress/WPPageHero.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Terms of Use',
  description: 'Mom Helper USA Terms of Use – Important Information and Policies regarding our services.',
};
---

<PageLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <WPPageHero title="Terms and Conditions" />

  <!-- Main Content Section -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl leading-relaxed space-y-8">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-normal mb-0 text-[26px] leading-[1.2em] text-black">
          Terms of Use – Important Additional Information
        </h3>
        <p class="mb-4 text-[#666666] font-medium text-[16px] leading-[2em]">
          Postpartum caregivers, babysitters (nannies), housekeeping helpers, and caregivers are all referred to as
          "caregivers".
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-2 text-[#666666] font-semibold text-[14px]">
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            After reviewing the sent contract, fill out and submit the service application form (reservation form) on our
            website. The contract is established once the reservation fee is deposited into the company's account. The transfer
            of the reservation fee is equivalent to agreeing to the contract terms.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            You cannot request tasks not decided upon at the time of the contract or unrelated tasks (e.g., picking up other
            family members, guest meal service, making kimchi, large amounts of ironing, washing bedding, cleaning the entire
            house).
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Basic service recipients include the mother, husband, and newborn for postpartum care, the respective child for
            babysitting (nanny) services, and the recipient (patient) for caregiver services. Additional charges may apply
            daily for other cohabiting family members.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            You must inform the company about the presence or planned installation of cameras in the house.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            For any changes related to work (e.g., change in working hours or days, change in job content, change of caregiver)
            after the start of work, please contact and discuss with the company.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Caregivers' rest time includes 3 hours for live-in caregivers and 1 hour for commuting caregivers (excluding
            night sleep, rest, sleep, jogging).
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Additional services are mandatory. If applicable, you must check this on the contract. Any adjustments or changes
            can be discussed and agreed upon with both the Mom Helper USA representative and the caregiver.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h5 class="font-normal mb-0 text-[18px] leading-[1.2em] text-black">Postpartum Care Additional Information</h5>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-2 text-[#666666] font-semibold text-[14px]">
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            If the mother wishes to extend or shorten the service period or replace the postpartum caregiver, she must consult
            with the company first.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Early Termination: If you wish to shorten the service period, please contact and discuss with the company. If
            the service is shortened after commencement, the remaining reservation fee (contract fee) will not be refunded.
            The caregiver must be informed at least 7 days in advance to avoid disrupting their schedule and plans.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Service Extension: If you wish to extend the postpartum care service, please inform the company at least 50%
            before the service ends.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            The primary duty of the postpartum caregiver is to care for the mother and newborn. As a postpartum helper, the
            caregiver provides some housekeeping services. (Tasks not directly related to postpartum care, such as cleaning
            the entire house, doing laundry for the family, washing bedding, large amounts of ironing, making kimchi, guest
            meal service, and preparing packed lunches, are not supported.)
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Additional charges may apply if you request tasks unrelated to postpartum care, such as preparing side dishes
            or laundry for other family members.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Services may change or be omitted based on the health status of the mother and newborn.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            If the baby's father is on a business trip, the caregiver may help with simple tasks like taking the older child
            to and from kindergarten, bathing them, and organizing toys, in consultation with the mother, and additional
            charges may apply depending on the situation.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h5 class="font-normal mb-0 text-[18px] leading-[1.2em] text-black">
          Additional Information about Babysitter and Nanny
        </h5>
        <p class="mb-4 text-[#666666] font-medium text-[16px] leading-[2em] font-semibold">
          Inform the company and the dispatched caregiver about your child's usual habits, playtime, feeding amount,
          feeding times, weaning food and snack times, bathing, personality, stranger anxiety, medical history, and
          emergency contact information.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h5 class="font-normal mb-0 text-[18px] leading-[1.2em] text-black">
          Additional Information about Babysitter and Caregiver
        </h5>
        <p class="mb-4 text-[#666666] font-medium text-[16px] leading-[2em] font-semibold">
          You cannot request tasks unrelated to the agreed duties at the time of contract (e.g., picking up other family
          members, doing laundry for other family members, guest meal service, making kimchi, cleaning the entire
          house).
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-2 text-[#666666] font-semibold text-[14px]">
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Inform the company and caregiver in advance about important information such as the guardian's contact information,
            children's or recipient's (care patient) hospital check-up schedule, allergies (food, medicine, etc.), and other
            crucial details.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            For any changes related to work (e.g., change in working hours or days, change in job content) after the start
            of work, please contact and discuss with the company.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h5 class="font-normal mb-0 text-[18px] leading-[1.2em] text-black">
          Service Contract and Cancellation Additional Information
        </h5>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-2 text-[#666666] font-semibold text-[14px]">
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            The service contract is established when the payment amount presented by the company is deposited into the bank
            payment account or via Zelle, and the contract is signed.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Cancellation by the Mother: The mother can cancel the reservation before the start of the postpartum care service
            in unavoidable circumstances. However, once the caregiver is decided upon through an interview, the reservation
            fee will not be refunded.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Cancellation by the Company: The company can cancel the reservation before the start of the service for unavoidable
            reasons, and in this case, the full reservation fee will be refunded.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-6">
            <span class="absolute left-0 top-[6px] text-[#d37643]">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 512 512"
                ><path fill="currentColor" d="M256 8C119 8 8 119 8 256s111 248 248 248 248-111 248-248S393 8 256 8z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            Reservation Change: In unavoidable cases, you can change the reservation before the service starts, and you must
            request this from the company operator at least 10 days before the start date of the service.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
